The '''São Tomé paradise flycatcher''' ('''''Terpsiphone atrochalybeia'''''), also known as '''São Tomé flycatcher''', is a species of bird in the family [[Monarchidae]]. The species was [[Species description|described]] by [[Thomas Richard Heywood Thomson]] in 1842, with ''Tchitrea atrochalybeia'' the [[Binomial nomenclature|binomial]] and [[Bioko|Fernando Po]] given as the [[Type (biology)#type locality|type locality]].<ref name="Thomson">{{cite journal |url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2324181 |title=Description of a new species of ''Genetta'', and of two species of Birds from Western Africa |author=[[T. R. H. Thomson|Thomson, T. R. H.]] |journal=[[The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Including Zoology, Botany, and Geology]] |year=1842 |volume=10 |issue=64 |pages=203–205 |doi=10.1080/03745484209445224}}</ref> The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[São Tomé Island]].<ref>[[BirdLife International]], [http://datazone.birdlife.org/species/factsheet/sao-tome-paradise-flycatcher-terpsiphone-atrochalybeia Species Factsheet ''Terpsiphone atrochalybeia''], accessed 17 January 2019</ref>
Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical dry forests and subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests.

